3. Executive Summary
3.1 Overview
The OSINT assessment identified a significant external attack surface. Publicly available information revealed exposed infrastructure, leaked credentials, hidden subdomains, employee information, development environments, and sensitive documents.
A motivated attacker could gather enough intelligence to perform targeted attacks without requiring insider access. The combination of exposed internet services, leaked GitHub secrets, publicly indexed documents, and vulnerable APIs substantially increases the likelihood of compromise.
More than 110 OSINT findings were collected, with nearly half directly exposing internal systems or sensitive information.

